<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-09-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-09-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3336: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Horn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-29T18:00:00-04:00">September 29, 1933—6
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 30—3:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>94. My 93, September 29, 10 a.m. I have just had presented to me the
                            following reply from the Minister of Foreign Affairs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The Paraguayan Government cordially thanks the American
                                    Government for its friendly interest in the satisfactory
                                    solution of the Chaco conflict and has the satisfaction of
                                    informing it that it has accepted without reservations the
                                    proposal of the mediators acting under mandate of the
                                    League.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Horn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>